Cybercrime Prevention Tips

1. Never share OTP, password, or bank details with anyone.
2. Always check website URL before entering login information.
3. Use strong and unique passwords for different accounts.
4. Enable two-factor authentication whenever possible.
5. Do not click on unknown links received in email or message.
6. Do not accept calls asking for UPI or bank details.
7. Verify UPI payment requests before approving.
8. Do not install apps from unknown sources.
9. Use antivirus and keep system updated.
10. Report cybercrime at cybercrime.gov.in or call 1930.